A Redwall Winter 's Tale was written by Brian Jacques and illustrated by the well - known Redwall artist , Christopher Denise . A Redwall Winter 's Tale is the second Redwall picture book . It features the molebabe Bungo and the citizens of Redwall trying to decipher more clever riddles . A Redwall Winter 's Tale opens up on the last day of autumn . At Redwall Abbey , dibbuns are playing outside when they notice a group of travelling performers approaching the Abbey . Everyone enters and a show is put on by the performers . Finally , when it is time for bed , the dibbun mole Bungo is told the story of the Snow Badger , a mythical creature who makes the snow fall . Later that night , Bungo sees the Snow Badger and is able to talk to him ! . When the little mole wakes up , he finds a pouch around his neck . It contains a small crystal drop , and a note is written on the inside of the pouch on a scrap of parchment . The Redwallers must to try to figure it out . . . Redwall • Mossflower • Mattimeo • Mariel of Redwall • Salamandastron • Martin the Warrior • The Bellmaker • Outcast of Redwall • The Pearls of Lutra • The Long Patrol • Marlfox • The Legend of Luke • Lord Brocktree • The Taggerung • Triss • Loamhedge • Rakkety Tam • High Rhulain • Eulalia ! . 